item.title: Structure-awared Visual-LiDAR Odometry and Dense Mapping
item.description: A Visual-LiDAR SLAM system considering both point, line and planar constraints. This system employ multi-sensor fusion and dense mapping in a same pipeline, which is robust under degenerated scenarios.

item.title: Map fusion method suitable for sub-map with few overlapping parts
Synthetic Data Generation for Multi-Robot SLAM
item.description: Time-synchronized simulation sensor data including LiDAR point cloud, stereo RGB images as well as IMU(Inertial Measurement Unit) data from multiple robots are recorded into ROS bags, which is sufficient for simulation tests for multi-robot SLAM systems.

item.title: LiDAR-based Collaborative Localization and Mapping
item.description: A system that uses multiple robots mounted with 16-beam LiDARs to build a 3D point cloud map of the environment.

item.title: Multi-unmanned-platform synchronous positioning and map construction method under limitation of communication bandwidth and distance
Embedding Temporally Consistent Depth Recovery for Real-time Dense Mapping in Visual-inertial Odometry
item.description:
A method to embed depth recovery algorithm into VIO-based sparse visual SLAM system for real-time dense mapping.

  • A subspace-based stabilization scheme to maintain the temporal consistency of visual landmarks.
  • A hierarchical pipeline for edge-preserving depth interpolation.
  • The whole pipeline is implemented using CPU only.

item.title: Embedding Temporally Consistent Depth Recovery for Real-time Dense Mapping in Visual-inertial Odometry
An Indoor Positioning System On Smart Phones
item.description:
A system to help users to localize themselves in a shopping center using a smart phone.

  • Image frames and gyroscope data are captured and upload to the server using an Android app.
  • Detect and track shop signs on image sequence.
  • Compute the positioning result and send it back to the user front-end.

item.title: Quick depth restoring method for three-dimensional reconstruction
Robust Visual Inertial Odometry With Consistent Sparsification
item.description:
A hybrid solution integrating the features of adaptive sensor fusion, robust loss function, and consistent sparsification into a visual-inertial odometry (VIO) system, improving the system’s accuracy, robustness, and efficiency respectively.

  • Switchable Constraints and Dynamic Covariance Scaling loss is use in visual residual to improve the robustness of the VIO system
  • The weights of inertial residuals are adjusted adaptively according to the motion states of the system
  • the marginalized information matrix is consistently sparsified to reduce the fill-in effect
